can my baby still be alive i was weeks pregnant last friday i started spotting which later became more like a period so i went to the er i was able to get an ultrasound done and they told me that that baby was fine although it was a threatened abortion that night i bled some more and i began to have cramps when i woke up i went to a different hospital this time they did another ultrasound this time the equipment was different more laserlike over my stomach like rather that the gel and the stick and she told me that the baby was still in my uterus but that it was on its way out to the vaginal area so i was told that i miscarried my boyfriend and i were devastated i bled till thursday my bleeding has stopped but it never got heavy and no blood clots or tissue of any kind discharged so what can it mean please help i really hate to tell you this but it doesn't sound good i've had two miscarriages myself i guess i can tell you how that went and maybe it will help you with my first pregnancy everything was fine up until week i was laying on the couch one day and i started getting these horrible cramps so i went to the er and they told me i had a threatened miscarriage and sent me home on bedrest for three days when i went to my obgyn two weeks later he told my i was going to miscarry well needless to say this wasn't the news i wanted to hear so i didn't except it i went to another doctor but heard the same thing they told me just to wait it out and when it happened i would know it about a week later i had horrible cramping for an entire day i went to bed that night and woke up in a pool of blood i woke my husband up and he took me to the er and sure enough four long painful hours later i miscarried two months later i got pregnant again this time around everything was perfect up until week and i was told i was going to miscarry again my doctor didn't want me going through the pain i had the first time so he did a d c i'm sorry to say that it sounds like you're in the same 